{"name": "podcastparser", "metadata": {"name": "podcastparser", "version": "0.6.10", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "http://gpodder.org/podcastparser/", "license": "ISC License", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Simplified, fast RSS parser", "upload_time": 1681824813}, "documentation": ["podcastparser: Simple, fast and efficient podcast parser\n========================================================\n\nThe podcast parser project is a library from the gPodder project to provide an\neasy and reliable way of parsing RSS- and Atom-based podcast feeds in Python.\n\nSee docs in [./doc](./doc) or at [Read the Docs](https://podcastparser.readthedocs.io/en/latest/).\n\n## Automated Tests\n\nTo run the unit tests you need [`pytest`](https://docs.pytest.org/).  If you have `pytest` installed, use the `pytest` command in the repository's root directory to run the tests.\n\n## Automated Release to Pypi\n\nTo release, update the version number in podcastparser.py, commit and push.\n\nThen create an (annotated) tag and push it.\n\nThe GitHub action will publish on pypi.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "podcastparser", "documentation": ["Simplified, fast RSS parser ", "-*- coding: utf-8 -*-", "Podcastparser: A simple, fast and efficient podcast parser", "Copyright (c) 2012, 2013, 2014, 2018, 2020 Thomas Perl <m@thp.io>", "Copyright (c) 2016, 2017, 2018, 2019, 2020 Eric Le Lay <elelay@macports.org>", "Copyright (c) 2020 E.S. Rosenberg <es.rosenberg+openu@gmail.com>", "Permission to use, copy, modify, and/or distribute this software for any", "purpose with or without fee is hereby granted, provided that the above", "copyright notice and this permission notice appear in all copies.", "THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED \"AS IS\" AND THE AUTHOR DISCLAIMS ALL WARRANTIES WITH", "REGARD TO THIS SOFTWARE INCLUDING ALL IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY", "AND FITNESS. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHOR BE LIABLE FOR ANY SPECIAL, DIRECT,", "INDIRECT, OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES OR ANY DAMAGES WHATSOEVER RESULTING FROM", "LOSS OF USE, DATA OR PROFITS, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT, NEGLIGENCE OR", "OTHER TORTIOUS ACTION, ARISING OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE USE OR", "PERFORMANCE OF THIS SOFTWARE."], "functions": [{"name": "podcastparser.file_basename_no_extension", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns filename without extension\n\n```pycon\n>>> file_basename_no_extension('/home/me/file.txt')\n'file'\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> file_basename_no_extension('file')\n'file'\n```\n"]}, {"name": "podcastparser.squash_whitespace", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "text", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Combine multiple whitespaces into one, trim trailing/leading spaces\n\n```pycon\n>>> squash_whitespace(' some           text  with a    lot of   spaces ')\n'some text with a lot of spaces'\n```\n"]}, {"name": "podcastparser.squash_whitespace_not_nl", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "text", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Like squash_whitespace, but don't squash linefeeds and carriage returns\n\n```pycon\n>>> squash_whitespace_not_nl(' linefeeds\\ncarriage\\r  returns')\n'linefeeds\\ncarriage\\r returns'\n```\n"]}, {"name": "podcastparser.parse_time", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Parse a time string into seconds\n\nSee RFC2326, 3.6 \"Normal Play Time\" (HH:MM:SS.FRACT)\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_time('0')\n0\n>>> parse_time('128')\n128\n>>> parse_time('00:00')\n0\n>>> parse_time('00:00:00')\n0\n>>> parse_time('00:20')\n20\n>>> parse_time('00:00:20')\n20\n>>> parse_time('01:00:00')\n3600\n>>> parse_time(' 03:02:01')\n10921\n>>> parse_time('61:08')\n3668\n>>> parse_time('25:03:30 ')\n90210\n>>> parse_time('25:3:30')\n90210\n>>> parse_time('61.08')\n61\n>>> parse_time('01:02:03.500')\n3723\n>>> parse_time(' ')\n0\n```\n"]}, {"name": "podcastparser.parse_url", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "text", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "podcastparser.parse_length", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "text", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Parses a file length\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_length(None)\n-1\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_length('0')\n-1\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_length('unknown')\n-1\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_length('100')\n100\n```\n"]}, {"name": "podcastparser.parse_type", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "text", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["\"normalize\" a mime type\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_type('text/plain')\n'text/plain'\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_type('text')\n'application/octet-stream'\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_type('')\n'application/octet-stream'\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_type(None)\n'application/octet-stream'\n```\n"]}, {"name": "podcastparser.parse_pubdate", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "text", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Parse a date string into a Unix timestamp\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_pubdate('Fri, 21 Nov 1997 09:55:06 -0600')\n880127706\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_pubdate('2003-12-13T00:00:00+02:00')\n1071266400\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_pubdate('2003-12-13T18:30:02Z')\n1071340202\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_pubdate('Mon, 02 May 1960 09:05:01 +0100')\n-305049299\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_pubdate('')\n0\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> parse_pubdate('unknown')\n0\n```\n"]}, {"name": "podcastparser.parse", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "url", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "stream", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "max_episodes", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Parse a podcast feed from the given URL and stream\n\n```\nparam url\n\nthe URL of the feed. Will be used to resolve relative links\n\nparam stream\n\nfile-like object containing the feed content\n\nparam max_episodes\n\nmaximum number of episodes to return. 0 (default)\nmeans no limit\n\nreturns\n\na dict with the parsed contents of the feed\n```\n"]}, {"name": "podcastparser.normalize_feed_url", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "url", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Normalize and convert a URL. If the URL cannot be converted\n(invalid or unknown scheme), None is returned.\n\nThis will also normalize <feed://> and itpc:// to http://.\n\n```pycon\n>>> normalize_feed_url('itpc://example.org/podcast.rss')\n'http://example.org/podcast.rss'\n```\n\nIf no URL scheme is defined (e.g. \"curry.com\"), we will\nsimply assume the user intends to add a <http://> feed.\n\n```pycon\n>>> normalize_feed_url('curry.com')\n'http://curry.com/'\n```\n\nIt will also take care of converting the domain name to\nall-lowercase (because domains are not case sensitive):\n\n```pycon\n>>> normalize_feed_url('http://Example.COM/')\n'http://example.com/'\n```\n\nSome other minimalistic changes are also taken care of,\ne.g. a ? with an empty query is removed:\n\n```pycon\n>>> normalize_feed_url('http://example.org/test?')\n'http://example.org/test'\n```\n\nLeading and trailing whitespace is removed\n\n```pycon\n>>> normalize_feed_url(' http://example.com/podcast.rss ')\n'http://example.com/podcast.rss'\n```\n\nIncomplete (too short) URLs are not accepted\n\n```pycon\n>>> normalize_feed_url('http://') is None\nTrue\n```\n\nUnknown protocols are not accepted\n\n```pycon\n>>> normalize_feed_url('gopher://gopher.hprc.utoronto.ca/file.txt') is None\nTrue\n```\n"]}, {"name": "podcastparser.is_html", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "text", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Heuristically tell if text is HTML\n\nBy looking for an open tag (more or less:)\n\\>>> is_html('\\<h1>HELLO\\</h1>')\nTrue\n\\>>> is_html('a \\< b \\< c')\nFalse\n"]}, {"name": "podcastparser.remove_html_tags", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "html", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Remove HTML tags from a string and replace numeric and\nnamed entities with the corresponding character, so the\nHTML text can be displayed in a simple text view."]}], "variables": [{"name": "podcastparser.__author__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "podcastparser.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "podcastparser.__website__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "podcastparser.__license__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "podcastparser.logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "podcastparser.MAPPING", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "podcastparser.VALID_ROOTS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "podcastparser.HTML_TEST", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "podcastparser.Target", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "podcastparser.Target.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "key", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "filter_func", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "overwrite", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "podcastparser.Target.start", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "handler", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "attrs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "podcastparser.Target.end", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "handler", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "text", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "podcastparser.Target.WANT_TEXT", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variable